Literature with Kim Il Sung's Portrait Distributed in Italy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 11 (KCNA) -- The Group of Dialectical Materialist Atheists of Italy distributed a literature bearing the portrait of President Kim Il Sung with a sunny smile across the country on the 11th anniversary of his demise.
 The literature said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 July 8 marks the 11th anniversary of the demise of President  Kim Il Sung, an outstanding statesman and peerlessly great man who made enormous contributions to the cause of the Korean people and the world people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His famous works were, are and will be a beacon that illuminates the road ahead of the Korean people in their arduous struggle for the independent and peaceful reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The scientific principles of the Juche idea founded by him and being brought into reality by leader Kim Jong Il are priceless wealth for us struggling to achieve liberation from exploitation, the right to labor and the right to acquire and enjoy science and culture, preserve the idea and morality of the working class and defend the motherland from aggression and interference.

Retaliation to GI Criminals Vowed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 11 (KCNA) -- The Headquarters of the Movement for the Withdrawal of the U.S. Forces reportedly released a statement titled "We warn sure retaliation when U.S. soldiers commit a crime" on July 7.
 Recalling that three U.S. soldiers belonging to the 2nd Division of the U.S. army beat a passing south Korean civilian named Jo Su Hwan on the face with a beer bottle, seriously wounding him, in Uijongbu, Kyonggi Province on July 2, the statement said the police, far from saving the fellow countryman, handed to the U.S. army the criminal and even gathered evidences, failing to make any investigation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Deploring the tragic fact, the statement called for taking a strong action against crimes of U.S. soldiers before it is too late, so that such incident may not occur again. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It warned that when U.S. soldiers commit violence or crime against Koreans, the retaliation will be twice harsher, the method being the same. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Announcing that preparations would get off to a start now to set up "a citizens' team of investigation into U.S. army crimes", the statement declared: We make it plain that we have the right to kill two U.S. soldiers, if they kill one Korean.

Yang Hyong Sop Meets Chinese Delegation and Manager of New York Times 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 11 (KCNA) -- Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, met and had a friendly talk with the delegation of the Chinese People's Association for Peace and Disarmament led by its Vice-President Liu Jingqin at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today.
 On hand were Kim Jin Bom, vice-chairman of the Korean National Peace Committee, and Wu Donghe, Chinese ambassador to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop met and conversed with Arthur Sulzburger, manager of the New York Times, and his party at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kim Yong Il, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs of the DPRK, and officials concerned.

U.S. Anti-DPRK Vituperation Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 11 (KCNA) -- The U.S. diplomatic boss in a recent radio interview, crying over DPRK's "nuclear threat," threw together the balderdash that north Korea cannot join the international community unless it abandons nuclear weapons.
 Categorically refuting this trash, a Rodong Sinmun commentary Monday says the United States is putting up an absurd argument, never stopping tongue-lashing over the "nuclear issue" of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The analyst continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is nonsensical for the U.S. to take issue with the "nuclear threat" from the DPRK. And linking the DPRK's "renunciation of nuclear weapons" with its "joining the international community" is contradictory to the nature of the matter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With the DPRK and the U.S. technically at war, no one can tell when the U.S. scheme to make a preemptive nuclear attack on the DPRK will be carried into action. It was not easy but painstaking for the DPRK to have an access to nuclear weapons while going through manifold difficulties imposed upon it by tightened sanctions and blockade by the enemy. However, the DPRK had no other option but to choose this in order to defend its idea and system, security and sovereignty from the U.S. moves to stifle it with nukes. It was a just defensive step, to all intents and purpose, to defend itself. Herein lies the reason why the DPRK has built its own nuclear deterrent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But the United States is turning an unseeing eye to the background and purport of the DPRK's accession to nuclear weapons. Wantonly distorting and exaggerating its nature and truth, the U.S. is trying to mislead public opinion by creating the impression that the DPRK is harboring "nuclear ambition" in a bid to brand it as a "nuclear criminal". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We do not intend to possess nuclear weapons forever. If the U.S. nuclear threat to the DPRK is removed and its hostile policy to "bring down the system" of the latter is withdrawn, not a single nuclear weapon will be needed to the latter. Since the DPRK has been compelled to possess nuclear weapons by the increasing nuclear threat from the U.S., it is quite logical that the U.S. nuclear threat to the DPRK and its hostile policy toward the latter must be retracted, if the nuclear issue is to be settled. This is the pivotal point and the main key to the settlement of the nuclear issue.

Maintenance of National Independence Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 11 (KCNA) -- National independence serves as a powerful weapon to achieve the reunification of the country and national prosperity, declares Rodong Sinmun in an article Monday.
 Noting that the consciousness of national independence and sentiments for independent reunification are growing among the Koreans day by day, the author of the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National independence is the key point in solving the national problem and shaping the destiny of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is impossible to think about the existence of the nation and its development away from independence. Only when the principle of national independence is firmly maintained is it possible to correctly solve the national problem and successfully shape the destiny of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National independence is also the lifeline in accomplishing the cause of the reunification of the country. Apart from it no one can talk about the reunification of the country or think of the common prosperity of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the Koreans join efforts, they can well achieve the reunification of the country and national prosperity and there will be nothing out of their reach. Unshakable is the will of the Koreans to steadily advance toward independence under any condition with the faith that reunification and prosperity can be achieved by national independence.

Fuller Play to Politico-Ideological Might Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 11 (KCNA) -- The politico-ideological might of the single-mindedly united revolutionary ranks is an engine for winning a sure victory in Korean-style socialism advancing under the banner of the Songun while foiling all moves of imperialists to isolate and stifle it. Rodong Sinmun Monday says this in signed article.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The leader, the party and the people are single-mindedly united in our society. This politico-ideological might of the Korean revolution has become a main source of winning steady victory in Korean-style socialism despite any storm and stress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il is a decisive factor of augmenting the politico-ideological might of the Korean revolution in every way as required by the era of Songun. 
 The headquarters of the revolution is the very core of the single-minded unity and it is a sure guarantee for glorifying Korean-style socialism to devotedly protect it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To devotedly defend the headquarters of the revolution serves as a slogan for practice and action for the servicepersons and people in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The politico-ideological might of the revolutionary ranks is being fully displayed by all the servicepersons and people in implementing the Party's line and policies in a do-or-die spirit in hearty response to its call. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This might represents strong revolutionary enthusiasm and creative ingenuity displayed by broad masses in carrying through the line and policies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This might also finds a vivid manifestation in the fact that all members of the society are working, helping and leading each other forward on the basis of collectivism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are united close on the basis of revolutionary comradeship, helping and leading each other forward in a big family whose members hold Kim Jong Il in high esteem as their father. Herein lie the politico-ideological might of the Korean revolution and advantages and invincibility of Korean-style socialism.

Anniv. of Demise of President Kim Il Sung Commemorated in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 11 (KCNA) -- Seminars, photo exhibitions and film shows were held in Bangladesh, Laos and Democratic Congo from July 2 to 5 on the occasion of the 11th anniversary of demise of President Kim Il Sung.
 On display at the exhibitions were photos showing the glorious and brilliant revolutionary life and immortal exploits of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the film show watched Korean film "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung Will Always Be with Us." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Figures of the Bangladesh People's League and the Bangladesh Self-Reliance Research Centre said at a seminar on the immortal Juche idea and development of the DPRK that Kim Il Sung fathered the Juche idea and wisely led the revolution and construction, adding that Korean-style socialism firmly based on the Juche idea is socialism which has achieved single-minded unity because the whole society is like a great family in which the leader and the Party, the army and people have formed a community linked with the same destiny. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the Laos-Korea Tin Company at a photo exhibition lauded Kim Il Sung as an outstanding leader of the world revolution who performed brilliant exploits for the country, the nation, era and humankind through his total dedication all his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of Kinshasa University said at a film show that though Kim Il Sung passed away, his exploits are immortal and he would be always remembered by the Congolese people.

Farm Machine Accessory Production Goes Up
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 11 (KCNA) -- Tractor accessory factories and trailed farm implement factories throughout the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have mass-produced various kinds of farm machine accessories.
 The tractor accessory factories in Chongjin, Sariwon, Jongju and Anju have boosted the production considerably. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The trailed farm implement factories in Haeju, Hamhung and Kwaksan produced more than 200,000 farm machines and their parts of ten-odd kinds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, they have improved the structures of farm machines to suit new crop seeds and cultivation methods, and invented new kinds of machines including an air bean sowing machine. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The working people in the agriculture-related field throughout the country are doubling their efforts in response to the slogans jointly issued by the Central Committee and Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea to greet its 60th birthday, calling upon all the sectors of the national economy to give the precedence to providing the agricultural domain with manpower, equipment and materials needed for farming.

Korean Women's Share in Social Progress
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 11 (KCNA) -- The women of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea are playing a big part in the social development.
 The issue of women had already been raised as a fundamental matter concerning the social revolution in the early period of the Korean revolution. Ample experience and exploits were gained and the idea on equality between sexes was formulated in the "Ten-point Programme of the Association for the Restoration of the Fatherland" during the anti-Japanese armed struggle. And the "Law on Sex Equality in North Korea" was promulgated on June 30, Juche 35 (1946). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The adoption of the first constitution of the DPRK in 1948 and the "Socialist Constitution of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea" in 1972 laid a solid legal foundation of sex equality and enabled the Korean women fully exercise their rights to independence and enjoy free state and social activities on an equal footing with men. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A lot of women have occupied important positions of the Party and government bodies. Women accounted for 20.1 percent of the deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly as of September 2003. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Having obtained a high degree of knowledge through over ten years of schooling, all the women participate in the independent and creative working life, giving full play to their talents in making social wealth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, more than 42 percent of the country's experts and technicians are women. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many women have made a great contribution to the development of science and technology and demonstrated the dignity and honor of the nation. Among them are Prof. and Dr. Kang Hui Ho, Dr. Hyon Yong Ra, "World Table-tennis Queen" Pak Yong Sun, "Marathon Queen" Jong Song Ok, WBCF champions Kim Kwang Ok, Ryu Myong Ok and Choe Un Sun and prize winner in the international concours "Art of the 21st Century" (piano) Yun Jin Bok. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the last five decades, hundreds of women have been awarded the title of the Hero of the DPRK and Labor Hero for their distinguished service for the prosperity of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In an interview with KCNA on the occasion of the "World Population Day" (July 11), Kang Nam Il, director of the Population Research Institute, said the role of the women in the DPRK will become greater as days go by to further promote the social development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year's theme is "equality".

KCNA Blasts U.S. New Move for Sanctions against DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, July 11 (KCNA) -- The U.S. recently launched one more offensive for sanctions against some economic institutions in the DPRK allegedly on suspicion of their involvement in proliferating weapons of mass destruction (WMD).
 By the president's administrative order the U.S. announced its plan to apply sanctions against companies of different countries including three economic companies of the DPRK, which it claims involved in the "plan for the development of WMD", and companies of other countries which have business relations with those companies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this regard the U.S. Department of Treasury said it would open to the public the charges against the enterprises which have had deals with the north Korean companies in question and names of those enterprises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is preposterous for the U.S. to fault ordinary economic institutions in the DPRK which have nothing to do with the proliferation of WMD and charge them with the manufacture, purchase, possession and development of materials related to WMD and their spread and of the missiles that can be used as delivery means for WMD. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through this move the U.S. seeks to cause enterprises in the DPRK suffer much from future foreign trade in a bid to block its way of earning foreign currency. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a foolish attempt to bar the inter-Korean reconciliation and cooperation and legitimate economic dealings with other countries with an eye to economically isolating and stifling the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 U.S. economic sanctions are part of its policy of interference and blockade against other countries. U.S. sanctions and economic blockade against the DPRK, in particular, have persisted for the last decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dozens of acts are now in force in the U.S. for imposing economic sanctions and blockade against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The laws enacted by the successive U.S. Congresses labeled any government of a country subject to sanctions as a "criminal government that violated international law" and this entailed a war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S sanctions against the DPRK have become more persistent and stringent since the outset of the new century.  It can not but draw attention to the fact that Washington has not made any slight retreat or concession as regards the economic sanctions against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is pointing an accusing finger at the principal dialogue partner at the six-way talks at a time when the international community wishes to see the Korean Peninsula denuclearized through the talks in an atmosphere of confidence and stability. This behavior cannot be interpreted otherwise than a departure from the elementary morality and ethics between states. 
 The DPRK has exercised patience and shown utmost prudence in the relations with the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Explicitly speaking, the U.S. new measure for economic sanctions against the DPRK will not help settle the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. but touch off bitterer hostility against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should bear in mind that the DPRK has never been deterred by any "pressure" as it is an independent sovereign state.
 Sanctions will get the U.S. nowhere.
